cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.DC 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with computation offloading in a cloud-radio-access-network (C-RAN) for Internet-of-things (IoT) applications, which involves networking and communication aspects. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the optimization of transmit power and resource allocation, which are related to information theory. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with the control of the MIMO C-RAN system to optimize computation offloading, which falls under the scope of systems and control. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a supervised deep learning method for computation offloading, which falls under the scope of machine learning. 
5. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper deals with computation offloading in a distributed system (C-RAN), which falls under the scope of distributed computing.
